{
  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, this work introduces the first automated CAD system for mass detection and classification in CESM images.",
    "Furthermore, the model also was evaluated on FFDM images.",
    "The INbreast and the newly introduced CDD-CESM datasets were used in the experiments.",
    "The conducted experiments showed that the CESM images could improve the CAD system's performance at both detection and classification levels, as they showed better results than FFDM images.",
    "The proposed model achieved detection accuracy of 98.96% and 81.52%; moreover, it achieved a classification accuracy of 95.65% and 97.61% for INbreast and CESM, respectively.The experiments also showed that the image size affected the detection results specifically for the CDD-CESM dataset as the image size of 640 enhanced the mAP for DM images by 3.4% and 9.8% for CE images compared to the image size of 416.The proposed model utilized the potential of the vision transformers with mammographic images in classifying the masses detected using YOLOv4."
  ]
}